<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="685" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1417</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-12"><hi rend="italic">March 12,
                                        1920</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 158</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my note No. 121 of
                                February 24th, I have the honour to inform you that His Majesty’s
                                Government intend to <pb facs="0780" n="682" xml:id="pg_682"/>
                                retain the services of General Beckett on the Technical Board so
                                long as Mr. Stevens remains at Harbin. His Majesty’s Government are
                                therefore anxious to ascertain whether Mr. Stevens is likely to
                                remain, and if so for how long.</p>
                            <p>I should accordingly be grateful if you could afford me some
                                information on this point to enable me to reply to the enquiry made
                                by the Foreign Office in London.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">R. C.
                                Lindsay</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>